Masters (MS) Business Analytics in Australia: Top Universities, Requirements and Scholarships

  • 234 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jun 07,2023 12:56 PM IST

Masters in Business Analytics in Australia is a popular business program equipping students with analytical skills useful in business planning. Read the blog to know everything about the program, admission requirements and available scholarship options.

Australia is a popular study-abroad destination known for its high-quality education system. The country has become a popular destination among international students seeking a masters degree in Business Analytics as the specially designed curriculum help students learn and develop analytical skills essential in the global market.

Like any other developed nation, education institutions in Canada also have certain admission requirements that students must consider before applying. Read the blog to learn everything about MS Business Analytics in Australia, along with details on the top universities in Australia offering the course, admission requirements and available scholarships.

Benefits of Pursuing Masters (MS) in Business Analytics in Australia

Quality Education: Australian universities are renowned for their high-quality education and research standards. Consistently ranking among top institutions globally, Australian universities ensure that students receive quality education and training in business analytics.

Global Recognition: Degrees from Australian universities are globally recognised, increasing graduates' employability in the international job market.
Support for International Students: Australian universities offer extensive support services for international students, including academic guidance, language assistance, career services, and housing support.

Cultural Diversity: Studying in Australia allows international students to experience different cultures, meet people from various backgrounds, and develop a global perspective, all of which are valuable in today's interconnected world.

Opportunity for Post-Study Work: Australia offers a Post-Study Work Visa for international students who have completed a degree there. It allows graduates to work in Australia for up to four years, depending on the qualification, providing an opportunity to gain valuable work experience and potentially transition to permanent residency.

Strong Job Market: Australia has a robust job market in data analytics and business intelligence.

Documents Required to Study Master (MS) in Business Analytics in Australia

To apply for Masters in (MS) in Business Analytics in Australia, students must keep certain documents in mind to make a successful application: While the requirement of documents sometimes varies from institute to institute, some general documents include:

  • Completed Application Form: Most universities accept applications for admission through an online system. Students should carefully fill in the personal, academic, and professional information to avoid any delay.
  • Passport Copy: Provide a copy of the identification page(s) of a valid passport.
  • Academic Transcripts: Official transcripts from all previously attended educational institutions are another important document required to apply for study in Australia. These should include a detailed record of academic performance, including courses, grades, and cumulative GPA.
  • Degree Certificates: Students are also required to provide degree certificates or provisional certificates in case the student is not yet graduated.
  • English Language Proficiency: Non-native English speakers need to prove their proficiency in the English language through tests like IELTS, TOEFL, or PTE test scores.
  • Statement of Purpose (SOP) or Personal Essay:  A well-written personal essay outlining the academic interests, career goals, and reasons for pursuing a Master in Business Analytics in Australia is another essential document. It simply helps the university to understand all the reasons behind choosing Australia as a study destination.
  • Curriculum Vitae (CV) or Resume (Optional): CVs or resumes are often requested from students to analyse their educational background, work experience, internships, skills, and achievements.
  •  Letters of Recommendation (LOR): Some universities also require students to submit letters of recommendation from professors, past employers, or other individuals who can attest their academic and professional abilities.
  •   GMAT or GRE Scores: Some universities require GMAT or GRE scores as part of the application process. So it is suggested to students to check the specific requirements for the chosen program before making an application.
  •  Financial Documents: Students may need to submit financial documents to prove that they have sufficient funds to cover their cost of living while studying abroad.

Masters (MS) in Business Analytics in Australia: Scholarships

Australian educational institutes offer numerous scholarships for international students. Some popular scholarships include:

  • Australian Government Research Training Program (RTP) Scholarships
  • Destination Australia Scholarships
  • Australia Awards Scholarships
  • University-specific scholarships and bursaries

Note: It is essential to connect with your study abroad consultant to research and apply for scholarships that best match your profile.

Popular Job Options after Masters (MS) in Business Analytics in Australia

The jobs mentioned below are just a few examples of the many job opportunities available to students graduating with a degree in Masters in Business Analytics.

  • Data Analyst
  • Business Intelligence Analyst
  • Data Scientist
  • Marketing Analyst
  • Financial Analyst
  • Supply Chain Analyst
  • Risk Analyst
  • Operations Research Analyst
  • Customer Analytics Manager
  • Management Consultant

Conclusion

Masters in Business Analytics from an Australian university can provide students with a strong foundation in data analysis, decision-making, and strategic planning. With a diverse range of top universities to choose from, students have ample opportunities to gain valuable skills and knowledge that can open doors to a successful career in the business analytics field. By researching universities, understanding admission requirements, estimating costs, and seeking scholarships, students can pave the way for a rewarding educational experience in Australia.

FAQ

What is the salary after MS in Business Analytics in Australia?
While the salary individuals earn is based on many factors, the average salary ranges between $100,000 and $130,000.
Is business analysis a demanding profession in Australia?
The Australian market has one of the highest-paid markets for Business Analysts compared to Canada, the UK and the USA.
What types of jobs are available for students after MS in Business Analytics?
Pursuing a masters degree in Business Analytics opens doors to a series of work opportunities in the fields of Machine learning engineering, Data architect, Data analyst, Chief technology officer, Chief data officer, Application architect, Project manager, etc.
What is the job of a business analyst in Australia?
Business Analysts conduct market analyses, analyse product lines and the overall profitability of the business. They also develop and observe data quality metrics while ensuring that business data and reporting needs are met.
How much CGPA is required for MS in Australia?
Different academic institutions in Australia have different CGPA requirements, so it is always suggested that students check with their study abroad consultant to verify all the details of the admission process.
